         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#chaniotis2012">
            <p>[The sarcophagus?] and the platform on which it stands belong
               to Marcus Aurelius Ammianos [son of - -], son of Alexandros,
               son of Nikeros, member of the tribe (?) [- -]; in this funerary
               site, which lies untilled and [- -] with a length of seven feet, and
               a width [in the front?] of four feet; in this (sc. sarcophagus) no
               other person [shall be buried except for] Ammianos [who is
               already buried here?] and Aurelius Zotikos [and - -].</p>
         </div>
